title: For Sale:  Citadel Compact - Excellent Entry Level 1911
postcontent:
For sale today we have a very nice Citadel Compact 1911 in .45 ACP caliber. For those not familiar with Citadel, it is the upper-tier 1911 line made by Armscor, makers of Rock Island Armory pistols. Citadel 1911's come with slightly different styling, a better finish, and ship with two magazines instead of only one as with RIA handguns. They are made on the same production line, and in fact, this pistol shipped with two magazines marked "Rock Island".I got this excellent all-steel pistol as a test and evaluation gun from the importer, and was so impressed with it that I bought it. It tested quite well and has been reliable and accurate with a number of different ammunition types. One of my staff assistants got it as his first 1911 and loved it, but has traded it back to me to help finance an upgrade to a Colt 1911. So, I have it for sale. The pistol comes with its factory box and two seven round magazines. Not included in the sale, but available as a package deal, I also have a set of right hand custom leather including a brand new IWB leather holster and matching magazine pouch, and three (3) Wilson Combat 7 round compact magazines, as well as some carry ammo. These items are not included in the price, but if you want them to complete your system, I will arrange deeply discounted pricing for them.
I will accept reasonable best offers on this firearm, but again, the operative word is "reasonable". All trades will be considered as well, but you will do better if you are buying the pistol outright with cash. postcontent: This early FAVORITE has a half round/ half octagon barrel with SILVER BLADE front sight and Flip up rear. Other milled-receiver AKs are machined from bar stock, but Arsenal’s hot-die hammer forging produces stronger and finer-grained steel. Internal voids and cooling deformations are eliminated by the 5-ton hammer forging process.
